{[showcards S:CQ]

You are West. The bidding has been as shown. You led the \D5, East wins the \DQ and returns the \D7. South holds up his \DA until the third round. He then plays the \CQ  

Play the \C8.

You assume (hope) that East holds the \CA. If he does then he will need help from you to decide which trick he should win. You play the \C8 first, and the \C2 next to show an even number.

If East is paying attention he will know to win the THIRD \C. This will kill dummy's \C suit, and with it South's chance of making 9 tricks.}
[Play "W"]D5

